<solution>
<p>First, distribute the $a to each term in the binomial:
  <me><math>$a $b x + 2 $a + $d x - $e = $solExpr</math>.</me></p>
<p>Next, combine like terms, moving constant terms to the right-hand side:
  <me><math>(<math simplify>$a $b</math> + $d) x = $solExpr - <math simplify>2 $a</math> + $e</math></me></p>
<p>Simplify:
  <me><math name="finalCoeff" simplify>$a $b + $d</math> x = <math name="finalRHS" simplify>$solExpr - 2 $a + $e</math></me></p>
<p>Finally, divide by $finalCoeff to solve for <m>x</m>:
  <md>
    <mrow><math>($finalCoeff x) / $finalCoeff</math> \amp= <math>$finalRHS/$finalCoeff</math></mrow>
    <mrow>x\amp= <math simplify>$finalRHS/$finalCoeff</math>.</mrow>
  </md></p>
</solution>
</problem>
